So during that time, there were certain things that happened like a church I'm about to

4
00:00:26.880 --> 00:00:32.080
go to the house and I was living there and certain things happened.

5
00:00:32.080 --> 00:00:38.800
So I would just very quickly relate the story from the beginning.

6
00:00:38.800 --> 00:00:48.200
And just to understand something about me, I can just say about getting my realization

7
00:00:48.200 --> 00:00:51.840
first, which is going to be very brief.

8
00:00:51.840 --> 00:01:01.040
So I used to seek through books while studying literature, but actually it was Mother Earth

9
00:01:01.040 --> 00:01:03.680
notebooks.

10
00:01:03.680 --> 00:01:13.840
It was Mother Earth notebooks that gave me my spiritual awakening in 1975 in Poland.

11
00:01:13.840 --> 00:01:19.400
From being an atheist overnight, I felt the presence of God.

12
00:01:19.400 --> 00:01:26.640
And from that moment, dramatic changes happened to my life.

13
00:01:26.640 --> 00:01:35.080
I was able to come to London in 1977 after seven years of applying for my passport just

14
00:01:35.080 --> 00:01:38.400
to leave the country.

15
00:01:38.400 --> 00:01:43.200
And then I continued my seeking in London.

16
00:01:43.200 --> 00:01:51.960
I went to various meditation groups and I was practicing Hatha Yoga as well until one

17
00:01:51.960 --> 00:02:03.840
day in 1980 in April, I arrived in Coxton Hall and I saw Shri Mataji for the first time.

18
00:02:03.840 --> 00:02:07.720
I had very strong experience during the meditation.

19
00:02:08.240 --> 00:02:17.120
To me, it was very obvious that I finally arrived at my destination.

20
00:02:17.120 --> 00:02:22.560
Of course, because the personality of Shri Mataji was also very magnetic and it was just

21
00:02:22.560 --> 00:02:29.520
impossible for me to do anything else except to follow her wherever she went.

22
00:02:29.520 --> 00:02:34.680
And she went to many places at the time because she was touring England.

23
00:02:34.680 --> 00:02:40.120
So I used to just sometimes travel at the back of her car and we all did.

24
00:02:40.120 --> 00:02:46.240
I don't know how we fit it in that car because it was a Mercedes, but sometimes seven of

25
00:02:46.240 --> 00:02:50.200
us, eight of us were in the car.

26
00:02:50.200 --> 00:02:54.400
So the car was expanding.

27
00:02:54.400 --> 00:03:05.120
So three weeks after I arrived, three weeks after my realization, I arrived in Dawliski

28
00:03:05.120 --> 00:03:08.800
Lashdam in London.

29
00:03:08.800 --> 00:03:15.120
And this was my first puja with Shri Mataji.

30
00:03:15.120 --> 00:03:21.200
And Shri Mataji asked me to decorate her feet and then I had to be in the heaven sitting

31
00:03:21.200 --> 00:03:24.200
on the floor for four hours.

32
00:03:24.200 --> 00:03:25.200
It was all getting dark.

33
00:03:25.200 --> 00:03:30.280
I didn't know how long it was going to last, but it was four hours.

34
00:03:30.280 --> 00:03:40.160
And of course, after leaving the ashram, I felt like a new person, completely free, feeling

35
00:03:40.160 --> 00:03:44.360
free, very happy and secure.

36
00:03:44.360 --> 00:03:56.200
So I felt I was sort of under Shri Mataji's wing, as to speak, because I don't know why,

37
00:03:56.200 --> 00:04:03.040
but Shri Mataji knew that I was feeling quite insecure anyway, didn't want to go back to

38
00:04:03.040 --> 00:04:04.040
Poland.

39
00:04:04.040 --> 00:04:11.120
So Shri Mataji used to hug me and kiss me quite often on seeing me.

40
00:04:11.120 --> 00:04:16.180
I just took it for granted and I thought it was always going to be like this.

41
00:04:16.180 --> 00:04:25.880
And when it stopped, I was quite disappointed, but somebody told me that I was ready to mature.

42
00:04:25.880 --> 00:04:35.160
But anyway, so it was really nice.

43
00:04:35.160 --> 00:04:44.360
My first time in Sahaja Yoga, however, sometimes I could not understand the accents of the

44
00:04:44.360 --> 00:04:49.600
Yogis because there were so many varied accents.

45
00:04:49.600 --> 00:04:57.280
And before I came, I used to spend most of my time with foreigners in London.

46
00:04:57.280 --> 00:05:05.040
So I could understand Shri Mataji's speeches very well, but I couldn't understand sometimes

47
00:05:05.040 --> 00:05:08.520
the Yogis with their very strong accents.

48
00:05:08.520 --> 00:05:18.480
Sometimes it was very hard for me to communicate, but nevertheless, in a couple of weeks after

49
00:05:18.480 --> 00:05:23.960
the puja, Shri Mataji suggested that I get married.

50
00:05:23.960 --> 00:05:31.120
There was a subtle reason for this, and I don't want to elaborate about it right now.

51
00:05:31.120 --> 00:05:36.680
I felt if I needed to marry, I would like to marry a good Yogi.

52
00:05:36.680 --> 00:05:46.360
I think it was me, not Pat, who was first asked by Shri Mataji about the marriage.

53
00:05:46.360 --> 00:05:50.640
So Shri Mataji said Pat was a very good person and she recommended him.

54
00:05:50.640 --> 00:05:58.140
So I said, yes, thank you very much.

55
00:05:58.140 --> 00:06:02.300
And I was wondering what will happen next.

56
00:06:02.300 --> 00:06:12.560
I saw Pat before at the ashram with his son, so I could feel this bond of love between

57
00:06:12.560 --> 00:06:14.560
both of them.

58
00:06:14.560 --> 00:06:22.020
And that was very perfect for me because I just thought I would have a family ready made.

59
00:06:22.900 --> 00:06:29.620
However, things were not that straightforward because my future husband was clearly avoiding me.

60
00:06:29.620 --> 00:06:36.860
So I thought it was not such a good start after all.

61
00:06:36.860 --> 00:06:46.820
I could see Yogis looking at me and whispering and meaningfully sort of giving me glances.

62
00:06:46.820 --> 00:06:52.540
So I thought something strange was really going on.

63
00:06:52.540 --> 00:06:58.300
A week also passed and I had no idea what was supposed to happen.

64
00:06:58.300 --> 00:07:03.060
We went with Shri Mataji to Hester's house in Hampstead.

65
00:07:03.060 --> 00:07:09.460
After I think it was a public program in friends meeting house in Hampstead.

66
00:07:09.460 --> 00:07:13.460
So after the program, we stayed overnight.

67
00:07:20.580 --> 00:07:23.820
We can't hear you again, Gresha.

68
00:07:23.820 --> 00:07:28.500
Alpana, I just wanted to remind you, have you put it on the speaker mode?

69
00:07:28.500 --> 00:07:33.100
Resna will be on the main screen when you're recording.

70
00:07:33.100 --> 00:07:38.900
So the view can be speaker mode.

71
00:07:38.900 --> 00:07:40.980
So shall I start again?

72
00:07:40.980 --> 00:07:41.980
No, no, it's OK.

73
00:07:41.980 --> 00:07:43.060
We're back a little bit.

74
00:07:43.060 --> 00:07:44.460
We missed a couple of minutes.

75
00:07:44.460 --> 00:07:45.940
Yes, just fine.

76
00:07:45.940 --> 00:07:48.940
Yeah, please continue.

77
00:07:48.940 --> 00:07:51.140
OK, so where was I?

78
00:07:51.140 --> 00:07:55.740
Ah, the pad was not communicating.

79
00:07:55.740 --> 00:07:59.980
And he left early in the morning on that day.

80
00:07:59.980 --> 00:08:07.740
And in Hester's house, there was a walking wardrobe.

81
00:08:07.780 --> 00:08:11.780
I don't know if anybody remembers that wardrobe.

82
00:08:11.780 --> 00:08:14.300
There was a walking wardrobe in the bedroom.

83
00:08:14.300 --> 00:08:24.380
And Shri Mataji called me into this wardrobe for a private conversation.

84
00:08:24.380 --> 00:08:29.420
She told me that with such marriages it's like this.

85
00:08:29.460 --> 00:08:33.060
There are 20 people in the room.

86
00:08:33.060 --> 00:08:40.140
And everyone wants a perfect match.

87
00:08:40.140 --> 00:08:47.380
So if everybody wants a perfect match, how is this possible?

88
00:08:47.380 --> 00:08:51.540
Then mother asked me if I still agreed to marry Pat.

89
00:08:51.540 --> 00:08:56.100
And of course, I said yes.

90
00:08:56.100 --> 00:09:00.660
We both left the walking wardrobe.

91
00:09:00.660 --> 00:09:06.420
And Shri Mataji announced the marriage as an engagement to begin with.

92
00:09:06.420 --> 00:09:19.540
And of course, I was wondering what Pat's reply would be because I don't know.

93
00:09:19.580 --> 00:09:27.540
Anyway, so Pat met me later on that day with a huge bunch of flowers smiling.

94
00:09:27.540 --> 00:09:33.100
And I thought, well, that was a good start.

95
00:09:33.100 --> 00:09:42.300
It is from him that I learn about the events of the past week and the reason why he was avoiding me.

96
00:09:42.340 --> 00:09:49.900
So he was not keen on the match as his previous marriage was 12 years before.

97
00:09:49.900 --> 00:09:59.300
It was a real disaster and there was no his fault in the marriage.

98
00:09:59.300 --> 00:10:03.860
So it was not Shri Mataji who told him about the match.

99
00:10:03.860 --> 00:10:10.980
It was Peter Pierce who was told by Shri Mataji to ask him.

100
00:10:10.980 --> 00:10:19.940
And Pat was caught by surprise and said, yes, of course, if mother wishes.

101
00:10:19.940 --> 00:10:23.380
But he was too mind about it.

102
00:10:23.380 --> 00:10:25.940
He decided to meditate on it.

103
00:10:25.940 --> 00:10:33.700
And to his astonishment, he felt the right heart melting and the vibrations becoming really strong.

104
00:10:33.700 --> 00:10:36.820
So he became keen.

105
00:10:36.860 --> 00:10:43.540
But there was another message from Shri Mataji cancelling the match.

106
00:10:43.540 --> 00:10:50.340
As mother said, he was not spontaneous enough saying yes.

107
00:10:50.340 --> 00:10:53.740
Just imagine what a roller coaster.

108
00:10:53.740 --> 00:10:57.740
He was devastated.

109
00:10:57.780 --> 00:11:00.300
He was devastated.

110
00:11:00.300 --> 00:11:11.500
And he was going for lonely walks pondering how many former matches he will have in Sahaja Yoga.

111
00:11:11.500 --> 00:11:20.580
He was writing letters to Shri Mataji saying if he wanted to get married, but if he was not spontaneous enough,

112
00:11:20.580 --> 00:11:24.980
it only meant he was caught by surprise.

113
00:11:25.020 --> 00:11:35.300
Until the morning of Shri Mataji's announcement, he did not know whether he was going to be married or not.

114
00:11:35.300 --> 00:11:38.900
Unfortunately, that morning he left early for work.

115
00:11:38.900 --> 00:11:45.220
So he only found out from the phone call that I was matched, not he was matched.

116
00:11:45.220 --> 00:11:54.820
To whom he asked the person on the phone and the person said, I don't know, I couldn't hear.

117
00:11:55.660 --> 00:12:06.660
So, anyway, that was quite funny, the whole story, but this is of course not the end of it.

118
00:12:06.660 --> 00:12:11.220
Anyway, we seemed to get on very well.

119
00:12:11.220 --> 00:12:16.020
So he decided to introduce me to his parents and his son Kevin.

120
00:12:16.020 --> 00:12:23.540
He was quite confident that it would be all right for me to visit his parents,

121
00:12:23.540 --> 00:12:30.580
despite my English, I was always very self-conscious about my accent and my English,

122
00:12:30.580 --> 00:12:35.540
because I was for a short time in the country, I was very nervous.

123
00:12:35.540 --> 00:12:47.060
So I guess what happened on the day of the visit, I lost my voice.

124
00:12:47.060 --> 00:12:50.100
I couldn't say anything.

125
00:12:50.180 --> 00:13:02.420
I was thanking the Divine for solving the situation, and to this day I think it was my saving grace.

126
00:13:02.420 --> 00:13:11.460
Anyway, during the engagement I briefly lived in Hampstead, in Mrs. Gulani's place.

127
00:13:11.460 --> 00:13:16.980
I probably some of you remember Mrs. Gulani and Mr. Gulani.

128
00:13:16.980 --> 00:13:30.020
They were the owners of the famous Temple of All Fates, in which we had many weddings and marriages in Sahaja Yoga.

129
00:13:30.020 --> 00:13:35.940
It was actually a Hindu temple with huge plastic statue of Shridurga on the altar.

130
00:13:37.460 --> 00:13:46.100
Yes, you can see in some of the videos, we tried to get rid of the statue, but somehow

131
00:13:46.100 --> 00:13:51.060
we didn't want to upset Mrs. Gulani, so it remained there.

132
00:13:53.060 --> 00:14:01.460
So this was the venue where many, as I said, many pudas and marriages took place in the very beginning.

133
00:14:02.180 --> 00:14:10.340
And Mr. Gulani and the husband were very respectful to Shri Mataji, and sometimes they used to attend the pudas,

134
00:14:10.340 --> 00:14:13.460
though they were not really yogis or not dictating.

135
00:14:15.620 --> 00:14:28.900
Anyway, I stayed at Mrs. Gulani's place for some time, but something amazing happened to us in London.

136
00:14:28.900 --> 00:14:37.620
It was around July when Cherchem Road was purchased by Linda Williams,

137
00:14:38.020 --> 00:14:42.580
and this was another miracle, as she said, she bought it having...

138
00:14:44.980 --> 00:14:55.460
The house was in need of renovation, and old lady was previously the owner of the house, and she hardly looked after it.

139
00:14:55.540 --> 00:15:09.700
So that was the situation, and it was great because it was the first ever ashram owned by a Sahaja yogi.

140
00:15:09.700 --> 00:15:17.620
It was our own. I was asked to move the shower tree afterwards, after it was bought.

141
00:15:18.340 --> 00:15:24.340
Linda, her husband, her daughter, and other yogis like Chaya and Regis,

142
00:15:25.220 --> 00:15:30.900
and Louis, Marcus, they were all living there. There were quite a lot of us living there.

143
00:15:32.340 --> 00:15:41.940
As Antua probably will remember, the place was not only needing repairs,

144
00:15:42.580 --> 00:15:49.780
it needed a lot of vibrational work because the vibrations were terrible.

145
00:15:51.940 --> 00:16:01.060
So we used to burn candles in every room, we went around with ajwan, we played mother's talks in every corner of the room.

146
00:16:01.060 --> 00:16:11.140
We had this, what you call this, tape recorders. We used to play talks in every room,

147
00:16:11.700 --> 00:16:20.900
and we said many mantras. I tried to take the negativity out through the window. How we did that?

148
00:16:20.900 --> 00:16:30.260
We had a left hand towards the room, and with the right hand out of the window we were taking the negativity.

149
00:16:30.260 --> 00:16:39.380
Actually it worked. I do recommend if you ever in trouble in places. So it was like this.

150
00:16:41.300 --> 00:16:49.540
She managed to vibrate lemons, chilies, coconuts, sugar, salt, honey, and giforas.

151
00:16:49.540 --> 00:16:55.860
So we could use all these things to work on the vibrations.

152
00:16:57.300 --> 00:17:02.820
And of course we were meditating, but it was quite difficult sometimes to meditate there.

153
00:17:02.820 --> 00:17:10.580
But it was getting better, and because we were in the collective it was great.

154
00:17:11.860 --> 00:17:17.460
However we tried to fix things, but whatever we mended,

155
00:17:19.780 --> 00:17:28.660
another thing used to fall apart. So it was actually like going a few steps upwards,

156
00:17:29.380 --> 00:17:38.180
a few and even more steps backwards. You have no idea. You are so lucky having the ashrams that you have now.

157
00:17:38.180 --> 00:17:49.140
It was, as it's been prophesized, it was the foundation establishing ruins,

158
00:17:50.100 --> 00:17:59.860
because it was a ruin. And of course we were told Sher Shamraut was the foundation of the New Jerusalem.

159
00:17:59.860 --> 00:18:03.860
So despite the difficulties we were honored to be looking after it.

160
00:18:05.140 --> 00:18:12.740
Shrimad Arji was greeted at one point at the doorway when she came for the first time.

161
00:18:12.740 --> 00:18:21.220
And there was a small Shribu Midevi Puja offered to her on the doorstep. Later on the offerings

162
00:18:21.220 --> 00:18:30.180
were put under the stone in front of the house, and she met her and she established Shri Ganesha there.

163
00:18:31.780 --> 00:18:39.620
So Shri Ganesha was established, and also the first child was born there in August.

164
00:18:40.100 --> 00:18:49.460
And this was another story, because I remember Linda had contractions while Shrimad Arji was speaking to her on the phone.

165
00:18:49.460 --> 00:18:56.100
And in the end Linda dared to say that she actually was having contractions,

166
00:18:56.100 --> 00:19:05.460
because the conversation was getting longer and longer. She said she was getting having contractions

167
00:19:05.460 --> 00:19:12.020
and she was just about to have a baby. Shrimad Arji said yes, she could feel the contractions

168
00:19:12.900 --> 00:19:21.060
and told Linda to call the ambulance. So interestingly the ambulance did not reach

169
00:19:22.500 --> 00:19:28.900
the Royal Free Hospital, which was on the other side of London. It stopped halfway

170
00:19:29.860 --> 00:19:39.300
and the baby was born in University College Hospital in central London.

171
00:19:40.820 --> 00:19:50.100
We stopped in emergency, because 10 minutes later Linda delivered a child, a boy child.

172
00:19:50.100 --> 00:20:02.500
So it was amazing, because I was present at the birth of the baby, and for me it was an amazing experience,

173
00:20:02.500 --> 00:20:08.740
as I was quite scared of having children on my own, thinking I'm not going to go through this.

174
00:20:09.460 --> 00:20:14.980
But after that it was so easy, so I just thought well that's not that scary.

175
00:20:15.460 --> 00:20:24.340
Anyway, so Linda's husband arrived much later at the hospital, because he went to Royal Free,

176
00:20:24.340 --> 00:20:32.020
where the baby was supposed to be delivered. Shrimad Arji named the boy Datatriya.

177
00:20:34.420 --> 00:20:43.700
Anyway, now the life in the ashram kept going on. We had one car in the ashram and it was Peter's yellow van,

178
00:20:44.580 --> 00:20:50.340
maybe somebody can remember that yellow van, which we use for

179
00:20:52.180 --> 00:20:58.740
buying food in bulk and also buying flowers, lots of flowers in Covent Garden Market every week.

180
00:20:59.940 --> 00:21:06.900
Myself and Chaya were not working. Chaya was an Indian yogini, very old yogini,

181
00:21:07.540 --> 00:21:16.660
not very old at the time, but now, and we were not working, so we could we could spend all our time

182
00:21:18.340 --> 00:21:25.780
in very basic kitchen, maybe you remember it was on the second floor, and we were cooking trimmings,

183
00:21:26.420 --> 00:21:34.740
doing washing up all day, and entertaining guests who were visiting all the time to see the new ashram.

184
00:21:35.540 --> 00:21:42.740
And we were actually exhausted, so once when Shrimad Arji rang,

185
00:21:43.940 --> 00:21:53.060
and she asked me how it was all going, because I was quite new, I tried to say the truth, so I said

186
00:21:53.060 --> 00:22:01.220
well it's all fine but we're not getting much help, we just... and Shrimad Arji told me off.

187
00:22:02.020 --> 00:22:08.980
She said you are creating a problem for me, you just sit down and watch it.

188
00:22:11.780 --> 00:22:17.620
So I did that and it became much better, because everything became...

189
00:22:19.700 --> 00:22:24.260
everybody started sharing the chores and everything became more collected.

190
00:22:25.140 --> 00:22:37.380
Anyway, now I'm coming to the description how the room where the wedding was going to take place

191
00:22:37.380 --> 00:22:44.900
was created. So this the extension which is part of the meditation room now was being built,

192
00:22:45.780 --> 00:22:52.900
and Shrimad Arji asked at one point, she asked the men to put down the concrete for the food,

193
00:22:53.860 --> 00:22:59.300
for the floor in the night. She said now you are putting down the concrete,

194
00:23:00.020 --> 00:23:06.340
and they worked all night using all kinds of strange lighting, I remember this happening,

195
00:23:07.780 --> 00:23:15.380
and it was actually very cold, it was also quite cold, so while all these preparations were going,

196
00:23:15.860 --> 00:23:23.540
on their way, Shrimad Arji called me one day and fixed the date of our wedding for the 5th of

197
00:23:23.540 --> 00:23:33.460
December. Well that was all great, but there wasn't a room to have the wedding in.

198
00:23:36.100 --> 00:23:43.300
For quite some time I was observing the building work not really progressing as fast as it should

199
00:23:43.300 --> 00:23:52.180
have for the wedding to take place. This was a very trying time to exercise my witnessing power,

200
00:23:54.260 --> 00:24:03.220
and I don't think I was doing very well. In the meantime one Irish girl who lived across the road

201
00:24:04.420 --> 00:24:11.460
and was coming to meditate with us fell in love with Mia, and on hearing about the upcoming

202
00:24:11.460 --> 00:24:22.580
wedding they both asked Shrimad Arji if they could get married too. Shrimad Arji was sort of

203
00:24:22.580 --> 00:24:30.580
agreeing but was not happy with me for being over enthusiastic about it and possibly

204
00:24:32.020 --> 00:24:38.900
encouraging it. I am not sure, but I think I was encouraging it because I wanted

205
00:24:38.900 --> 00:24:48.340
as many people to get married as possible. So yeah, unfortunately the marriage

206
00:24:49.380 --> 00:24:56.500
of Mia only lasted three weeks. When he left Sahachi Yoga and Mia decided that being single

207
00:24:56.500 --> 00:25:04.420
was the easiest and safest option for him. So it's better not to fix other people's marriages

208
00:25:04.420 --> 00:25:13.540
and yourselves. The time of my wedding was approaching but the roof was nowhere to be seen

209
00:25:14.580 --> 00:25:23.940
and the walls were not plastered at all. They were just bare bricks. Nothing was much happening

210
00:25:25.780 --> 00:25:31.940
and it was a cold December. I was thinking the wedding would not take place at all.

211
00:25:32.180 --> 00:25:42.820
One day I was quite depressed thinking

212
00:25:44.820 --> 00:25:53.620
