00:51:50.080 --> 00:51:51.080
It was always like this with Shri Mataji.

444
00:51:52.080 --> 00:51:55.080
It was a different dimension to everything.

445
00:51:57.080 --> 00:52:01.080
It was very nice that you showed this, Greshene,

446
00:52:02.080 --> 00:52:04.080
because so often people don't realize,

447
00:52:05.080 --> 00:52:08.080
we just watch Mother's Talks and public programs

448
00:52:08.080 --> 00:52:15.080
and you don't get to see this very human, very beautiful, generous, laughing side.

449
00:52:16.080 --> 00:52:19.080
Shri Mataji would make jokes all the time, laugh things,

450
00:52:20.080 --> 00:52:24.080
and she had such a command and control over the whole atmosphere

451
00:52:25.080 --> 00:52:27.080
and our moods and our emotions.

452
00:52:28.080 --> 00:52:31.080
She could just change the mood of the room just like that,

453
00:52:32.080 --> 00:52:35.080
with some funny joke or something.

454
00:52:35.080 --> 00:52:39.080
It was always correct, according to the person.

455
00:52:40.080 --> 00:52:47.080
I still have the plates and I still welcome everybody to my house

456
00:52:48.080 --> 00:52:51.080
and I serve the meals from those plates.

457
00:52:52.080 --> 00:52:57.080
So, these presents were chosen specifically by Shri Mataji?

458
00:52:58.080 --> 00:53:02.080
I think they were brought from India.

459
00:53:02.080 --> 00:53:07.080
You see, this is special because my plates were like a leaf.

460
00:53:08.080 --> 00:53:11.080
There is a special thing. I should have brought it with me.

461
00:53:12.080 --> 00:53:16.080
It's important to understand the symbolism of the presents.

462
00:53:17.080 --> 00:53:21.080
Whenever Shri Mataji gave you a present, there was always a much deeper meaning behind it.

463
00:53:22.080 --> 00:53:27.080
The one I remember so vividly was the Guru Nanak Puja.

464
00:53:28.080 --> 00:53:29.080
I think it was 1980-81.

465
00:53:29.080 --> 00:53:32.080
Again in Hampstead at the All Temple Faiths.

466
00:53:33.080 --> 00:53:36.080
After this puja, Shri Mataji suddenly said,

467
00:53:37.080 --> 00:53:38.080
it's time for the gifts now.

468
00:53:39.080 --> 00:53:45.080
The young men brought in boxes of gifts and each gift was wrapped in a brown paper bag.

469
00:53:46.080 --> 00:53:49.080
So you couldn't see what was the gift at all.

470
00:53:50.080 --> 00:53:54.080
Shri Mataji would literally pick out one of these bags and say,

471
00:53:55.080 --> 00:53:57.080
this is for Patti, this is for so and so.

472
00:53:57.080 --> 00:53:59.080
That person would come up and get the gift.

473
00:54:00.080 --> 00:54:03.080
You'd see them coming, going back to their place, opening the bag.

474
00:54:04.080 --> 00:54:10.080
Each person would just kind of go, oh wow, each gift touched in some special place.

475
00:54:11.080 --> 00:54:14.080
One of the ladies, she said it was a bottle of perfume.

476
00:54:15.080 --> 00:54:20.080
She said, oh, this is because Mother is telling me that I must respect and love myself.

477
00:54:20.080 --> 00:54:29.080
It was just incredible to see how Shri Mataji knew each bag, what was in it, who it was for.

478
00:54:30.080 --> 00:54:32.080
We couldn't see at all. It was very sweet.

479
00:54:33.080 --> 00:54:36.080
But that was such a huge part of Shri Mataji, the generosity.

480
00:54:37.080 --> 00:54:39.080
This became a tradition.

481
00:54:40.080 --> 00:54:43.080
After pujas, especially in Kabbalah or the big pujas,

482
00:54:43.080 --> 00:54:52.080
so much of the puja money that was collected went to buying presents for all the hosting countries and the people who were hosting.

483
00:54:53.080 --> 00:55:02.080
I remember somebody coming back, having hosted an international puja from North America.

484
00:55:02.080 --> 00:55:16.080
She had been given gifts by Shri Mataji to bring back and distribute to the ladies in the country, in Canada and in North America, who hadn't been able to go.

485
00:55:17.080 --> 00:55:23.080
It was a very deep symbol.

486
00:55:23.080 --> 00:55:33.080
Shri Mataji really showed us how to be generous, how to be gracious, how to be generous, how to be a Lakshmi.

487
00:55:34.080 --> 00:55:37.080
It was very beautiful. It was a lovely, lovely day.

488
00:55:38.080 --> 00:55:44.080
I have also stories about perfume because you trigger this story, this memory.

489
00:55:45.080 --> 00:55:53.080
We were in Churchham Road. Have I got time to tell this little story?

490
00:55:54.080 --> 00:55:56.080
Yes, of course.

491
00:55:57.080 --> 00:56:05.080
We were at Churchham Road. I was following, obviously, Gresham with my family there for two years.

492
00:56:05.080 --> 00:56:16.080
One day, I remember there were little problems in the ashram, as it is. Sometimes it happens in collective life.

493
00:56:17.080 --> 00:56:24.080
We were not many there. We were there with Janet Ridley and her husband and my family with our five children.

494
00:56:25.080 --> 00:56:31.080
We already were seven there, which was occupying the whole last floor, top floor.

495
00:56:31.080 --> 00:56:43.080
Yes, the house was exactly a little bit more decorated than when Breschner was there.

496
00:56:44.080 --> 00:56:57.080
You made me so much smile, Breschner, because I do remember the bathroom without any heating and me bathing my children in our bedroom because it would have been far too cold for them.

497
00:56:57.080 --> 00:57:06.080
It was really a little bit of a tapasya to live in this ashram at the time.

498
00:57:07.080 --> 00:57:15.080
The kitchen was very basic, etc. The stairs were quite dangerous because some spindles were missing.

499
00:57:15.080 --> 00:57:22.080
It was early on. I just had my babies, but there were some things.

500
00:57:23.080 --> 00:57:33.080
Shrimataji knew, so she called us and she called me at the ashram with the phone, which was on the wall on the ground floor.

501
00:57:34.080 --> 00:57:39.080
She said, hello, Antoinette, this is Shrimataji here. I said, oh my God, Shrimataji.

502
00:57:39.080 --> 00:57:45.080
I said, I want to see you. Come and see me at my place.

503
00:57:46.080 --> 00:57:51.080
She was living then in an apartment near Victoria.

504
00:57:52.080 --> 00:57:59.080
I said, oh my God. I found somebody to look after the children, the babies then.

505
00:57:59.080 --> 00:58:13.080
I remember I was rummaging in my cupboard to match my tights to my skirt to look really nice in front of Shrimataji.

506
00:58:14.080 --> 00:58:21.080
I had a nice navy blue kind of three-quarter skirt, which was very elegant and then a top also elegant.

507
00:58:21.080 --> 00:58:26.080
But I took a little bit of time and then I said, oh my God, I don't want to be late.

508
00:58:27.080 --> 00:58:32.080
I really walked very fast to the tube station, which was Stockwell.

509
00:58:33.080 --> 00:58:38.080
There were only two stops. There was Stockwell and then another one. Then it was Victoria.

510
00:58:39.080 --> 00:58:44.080
I arrived there and I was a little bit out of breath arriving there.

511
00:58:44.080 --> 00:58:51.080
The servant opened the door and I was shown into the living room. I sat down.

512
00:58:52.080 --> 00:59:00.080
Shrimataji came in and I was a bit short of breath and I was so thirsty because of walking fast.

513
00:59:01.080 --> 00:59:05.080
Shrimataji looked at me with a kind of smile and she said,

514
00:59:05.080 --> 00:59:16.080
you don't need to match your tights to your skirt before coming to see me, but I have time to do a foot soak.

515
00:59:17.080 --> 00:59:19.080
She laughed and we laughed.

516
00:59:20.080 --> 00:59:25.080
At that point, she knew everything actually.

517
00:59:26.080 --> 00:59:32.080
I didn't even need to tell her the story of what was happening.

518
00:59:32.080 --> 00:59:41.080
Very sweetly, she said, see Antoinette, when there is a situation, I let it develop and grow.

519
00:59:42.080 --> 00:59:51.080
Then like a wave crashing onto the shore, I come forcefully with my vibrations.

520
00:59:52.080 --> 00:59:59.080
So there it was. You just need to witness. Then she sought everything out.

521
00:59:59.080 --> 01:00:07.080
Then she invited my husband and I for dinner with her in her dining room.

522
01:00:08.080 --> 01:00:16.080
I still remember some delicious mango wessel and she talked to us very sweetly, very kindly.

523
01:00:17.080 --> 01:00:25.080
Then she gave us a box, a little red box with four perfumes in it, Indian perfumes.

524
01:00:25.080 --> 01:00:38.080
I still have them. One is Mowbras, one is Kush, the green kind of perfume for Sri Ganesha, and the other one is Honey Circle.

525
01:00:39.080 --> 01:00:49.080
Actually, the other day I put some of the Honey Circle on her photograph and the vibration, the whiff of this perfume was wonderful.

